tt-toplike (0.4.1) noble; urgency=medium

  * tt-toplike-app: fix VT100 pending-wrap (deferred auto-wrap) in the PTY
    screen renderer.  Characters printed at the last column now correctly defer
    the row advance until the next printable byte; escape sequences (cursor
    moves, SGR) issued between two printable characters no longer displace the
    cursor onto the wrong row, eliminating the garbled line-break artefacts.
  * Drop tt-toplike-egui package; replaced by tt-toplike-app which hosts
    tt-toplike-tui inside a PTY window (eframe) instead of reimplementing the
    visualizations in egui widgets.
  * HybridBackend: direct subprocess polling (no shell wrapper) with arc-swap
    for lock-free SMBUS snapshot delivery to the render thread.
  * EMA smoothing now handles hex-format SMBUS values ("0x10e7a", "0x3e80")
    via try_parse_numeric(); previously all hex fields were silently skipped.
  * Starfield initialised with content-area dimensions so stars are centred
    in the visible widget, not in the full terminal buffer.

 -- Tenstorrent <software@tenstorrent.com>  Thu, 17 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

tt-toplike (0.4.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * HybridBackend: sysfs provides real-time core metrics (temp, power, voltage)
    while tt-smi is polled every 5 seconds in a background thread to populate
    SMBUS telemetry (DDR status, ARC health, board IDs). Zero blocking on the
    main render loop. Exposed as --backend hybrid; falls back to sysfs-only if
    tt-smi is absent.
  * BoardTopology: groups chips by SMBUS board_id (fallback to consecutive-index
    pairs when board_ids are unavailable). Exposes same_board(), board_hue(),
    board_label(). Hue palette: blue-cyan (200°), orange (20°), magenta (290°),
    green (110°).
  * sync_score(): geometric mean (a*b).sqrt() replaces abs(power_diff)/50 for
    inter-chip stream intensity. Intra-board pairs carry a 0.2 floor so links
    between on-board chips are always visible even under equal load.
  * Starfield board-aware streams: intra-board streams use ─ and board hue;
    inter-board use ═ and full rainbow sweep. Intensity driven by sync_score.
  * Memory Castle board separators: ║ in amber-gold (RGB 200,160,60) at board
    boundaries; │ in dim grey within the same board. Board label row added above
    per-device headers when ≥ 2 boards detected.
  * Arcade header topology diagram: one-line diagram shows chip blocks with
    activity bars (█▓▒░·), ←→ for intra-board links, ═══ for inter-board.
    Header expands to 4 rows when device_count ≥ 2 to accommodate diagram.
  * ArcadeVisualization.initialize_topology() wires topology into starfield and
    memory castle sub-visualizations at startup.
  * Auto-detect order updated: Hybrid → Sysfs → JSON → Mock (when both sysfs and
    tt-smi are reachable, Hybrid is preferred).

 -- Tenstorrent <software@tenstorrent.com>  Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

tt-toplike (0.3.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Full rainbow color cycling in Memory Castle: particle hues now sweep the
    complete 360° spectrum (was limited to 0-180°, producing only yellows and
    oranges). All four particle types (Read/Write/CacheHit/Miss) cycle together
    as a tetrad offset by 90°.
  * Background layers in Memory Castle now animate: DDR, L2, L1, and Tensix
    layer hues drift continuously rather than being hardcoded static colors.
  * Trail brightness raised from near-black (val ≤ 0.3) to visible ribbons;
    glyphs lifted from saturation 0.4/value 0.3 to 0.9/0.62 with hue animation.
  * Arcade mode @-hero now actually rendered on screen: overlay_hero() was a
    deliberate no-op (TODO comment); replaced with splice_char() implementation
    that places @ and its temperature-colored trail into the composite canvas.
  * Memory Flow DDR channel bars now grounded in SMBUS training status:
    trained channels show real current/power utilization bars, training channels
    animate with ◐◑/◒◓ spinners, untrained show dim outlines. Removed the
    synthetic frame-counter scan that implied per-channel data it didn't have.
  * Added README section: "How visualizations are grounded in hardware activity"
    covering LLM inference vs video generation patterns, idle baseline activity,
    and the tt-smi -r reset light show sequence.

 -- Tenstorrent <software@tenstorrent.com>  Wed, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

tt-toplike (0.1.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging for Ubuntu 24.04 (Noble Numbat).
  * Ships two binary packages:
    - tt-toplike: TUI monitoring tool (tt-toplike-tui binary)
    - tt-toplike-egui: GPU-accelerated egui dashboard
  * Safe-by-default backend chain: sysfs → json → mock (Luwen never
    auto-detected; use --backend luwen only when hardware is idle).
  * Visualization modes: --mode arcade|castle|starfield|flow|normal
  * Recommends tt-smi (TT PPA) for JSON backend; tenstorrent-dkms for sysfs.
  * Crates vendored under vendor/ for reproducible offline builds.

 -- Tenstorrent <software@tenstorrent.com>  Thu, 10 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
